From 15cffde4e88baf6e0e71d12fe8556b3a0ee46231 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Shreedhar Parande <sparande@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 12 Jun 2025 18:39:57 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:CP:hostapd: Enable Beacon Report caching and User
 access to it via CLI

Currently, RRM Beacon Reports received from a STA via the
Beacon Report Response frame are not stored in hostapd.
As a result, users have no way to retrieve or view these
reports.

Add support to store each Beacon Report in a list
received from a Beacon Report Response frame.

Use this list to provide previously received Beacon Reports
when queried by the user.

Clear the list each time the AP sends a new Beacon Report
Request to ensure only fresh reports are stored and returned.

Add a CLI GET command to allow users to dump the stored
Beacon Reports.

Sample output:
root@OpenWrt:/# hostapd_cli -i phy00-mld1_link1 show_rrm_beacon_report
bssid=00:03:7f:12:3a:3a op_class=0 chan=36 start_time=1385954918460 dur=200 report_info=42 rcpi=206 rsni=206 ant_id=0 parent_tsf=143741
bssid=00:03:7f:09:00:37 op_class=0 chan=36 start_time=1752138035260 dur=200 report_info=0 rcpi=172 rsni=172 ant_id=0 parent_tsf=143741
bssid=00:03:7f:63:a4:37 op_class=0 chan=36 start_time=293918105859 dur=200 report_info=0 rcpi=213 rsni=213 ant_id=0 parent_tsf=143741
bssid=00:03:7f:01:58:35 op_class=0 chan=36 start_time=16723965574836 dur=200 report_info=255 rcpi=182 rsni=182 ant_id=0 parent_tsf=143741

Patch-dependency: None
Patch-work: None

Internal-review: [PATCH v3] hostapd: Enable Beacon Report caching and User access to it via CLI

Signed-off-by: Shreedhar Parande <sparande@qti.qualcomm.com>
